<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-04-23"><hi rend="italic">April 23,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Reports that an edict provides for the removal of the governor of
                            Kiangsi from office and the punishment of the provincial judge and
                            treasurer on account of the riot at Nan-ch’ang.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>